    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-24T13:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-24T13:31:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762A.00/7–2454: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 248<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Office of the United States High Commissioner for
                            Germany</gloss>, at Bonn</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d248fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_KHJ1"
                            >Kellermann</persName> and cleared in draft with <persName
                            corresp="#p_LGW1">Lewis</persName>, <gloss target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>,
                        and <gloss target="#t_P1">P</gloss>. Repeated to Berlin.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-24T14:31:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1954—2:31 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. Re <persName corresp="#p_JO1">Otto John</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d248fn2">On July 21 Berlin had reported that <persName
                            corresp="#p_JO1">Otto John</persName> had disappeared and had been
                        missing since 10 p.m. July 20. (Telegram 44, 762A.00/7–2154) On July 22 in a
                        memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_LCB1">Lyon</persName> stated that <persName corresp="#p_JO1"
                            >John</persName> “would undoubtedly be very useful if he fell into the
                        hands of the other side.” (762A.00/7–2154)</note> Department in consultation
                    other interested agencies developed following position: <list>
                        <label>1)</label>
                        <item>Imperative that in answer press inquiries Secretary, <gloss
                                target="#t_HICOM1">HICOMer</gloss>, <persName corresp="#p_AK1"
                                >Adenauer</persName> and other Federal Republic authorities follow
                            same line.</item>
                        <label>2)</label>
                        <item>Utilizing anticipated official Federal Republic statement as peg, we
                            shall take position in answer press inquiries that: <list>
                                <label>a)</label>
                                <item>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_JO1">John</persName> German official and
                                    Government Federal Republic has made statement (or it our
                                    expectation statement forthcoming);</item>
                                <label>b)</label>
                                <item>All evidence points fact <persName corresp="#p_JO1"
                                        >John</persName> being held Soviet Zone against will.
                                    Certainly not acting like free man. (This will <pb facs="0620"
                                        n="586" xml:id="pg_586"/> make gratuitous any discussion of
                                    whether or not this a voluntary defection.)</item>
                                <label>c)</label>
                                <item>If questioned whether he knew much about US intelligence
                                    activities Germany we shall simply state <persName
                                        corresp="#p_JO1">John</persName> in charge internal security
                                    Federal Republic. Beyond this have no knowledge.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>3)</label>
                        <item>Essential no member Department and <gloss target="#t_HICOG1"
                                >HICOG</gloss> Bonn and Berlin speculate on subject <persName
                                corresp="#p_JO1">John</persName> publicly or with
                            correspondents.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
